items.jobDescribe:
1.Independently handle the employee life-cycle process (DL/IDL/intern/employee recruiting, pre- &amp; on-boarding, contracting, filing, orientation, exit, retention, etc) in a timely manner to meet internal customer requirements/needs;
2.Maintain and update the employee information in HRIS and ensure the data accuracy;
3.Manage and administer the performance evaluation and review process;
4.Collect the market salary and benefit benchmark and provide relevant analysis;
5.Local and global HR projects rollout and implementation;
6.Keep legislation update regarding labor laws and ensure company policies/rules/practices are in line with labor laws and regulations to help build up harmonious work place;
7.Handle employee complaints labor disputes/conflicts and deal with labor arbitration to maintain a healthy work relationship;
8.Develop company culture to help promote employee commitment and engagement;
9.Act as backup to trainer, C&amp;B and Admin and provide support when needed;
10.Help to develop &amp; implement Employee Engagement/ Communication events;
11.Any ad hoc work assigned by line manager.
